1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION directing the Legislative Research Commission
2 to establish the Nontraditional Instruction and Virtual Instruction Models Task Force.
3 WHEREAS, the use of technology in education has become more prevalent over
4 the past decade; and
5 WHEREAS, nontraditional instruction days have been used throughout Kentucky
6 school districts since the 2013-2014 school year; and
7 WHEREAS, a full-time virtual school has been in place in Cloverport Independent
8 School District since 2023; and
9 WHEREAS, the General Assembly has the responsibility for ensuring all students
10 in Kentucky receive access to a quality education that prepares them for future success;
11 and
12 WHEREAS, the General Assembly seeks to determine the benefits, advantages, and
13 disadvantages of virtual, electronic, or alternative instruction that is provided either for
14 short periods of time or as the single source of instruction for a school year;
15 NOW, THEREFORE,
16 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
17 Kentucky, the House of Representatives concurring therein:
18 Section 1. The Legislative Research Commission is hereby directed to establish
19 the Nontraditional Instruction and Virtual Instruction Models Task Force. The task force
20 shall investigate and make recommendations regarding:
21 (1) How effective nontraditional instruction days and virtual instruction models
22 are for students in each of the grade ranges, primary through fifth grade, sixth through
23 eighth grade, and ninth through twelfth grade;
24 (2) How prevalent the use of nontraditional instruction days and virtual
25 instruction models are in districts throughout the state and are those nontraditional days
26 used efficiently and effectively;
27 (3) How equipped teachers are to provide appropriate instruction on
