1 nontraditional instruction days and using virtual instruction models;
2 (4) How do nontraditional instruction days and virtual instruction models impact
3 learning outcomes for various groups of students, including but not limited to English
4 language learners, exceptional children, and at-risk students; and
5 (5) What adjustments to the support education excellence in Kentucky program
6 are needed to accurately reflect actual costs, including possible cost savings incurred, by
7 school districts while using nontraditional instruction days or virtual instruction models.
8 Section 2. The Nontraditional Instruction and Virtual Instruction Models Task
9 Force shall be composed of the following eight members with final membership of the
10 task force being subject to the consideration and approval of the Legislative Research
11 Commission:
12 (1) Three members of the House of Representatives to be appointed by the
13 Speaker of the House, one of whom shall be designated to serve as co-chair;
14 (2) Three members of the Senate to be appointed by the President of the Senate,
15 one of whom shall be designated to serve as co-chair;
16 (3) One member of the House of Representatives to be appointed by the Minority
17 Floor Leader of the House of Representatives;
18 (4) One member of the Senate to be appointed by the Minority Floor Leader of
19 the Senate;
20 Section 3. The Nontraditional Instruction and Virtual Instruction Models Task
21 Force shall meet at least monthly during the 2025 Interim of the General Assembly and
22 shall submit its findings and recommendations to the Legislative Research Commission
23 for referral to the appropriate committee or committees by December 1, 2025.
24 Section 4. Provisions of this Resolution to the contrary notwithstanding, the
25 Legislative Research Commission shall have the authority to alternatively assign the
26 issues identified herein to an interim joint committee or subcommittee thereof, and to
27 designate a study completion date.
